

This will add the JSF we did before and add to it an EJB layer.

You will notice I am doing an InitalContext lookup as well.
This is in general not a best practice. It was done more to show options than anything else.

Also you will notice there is no validaiton.
So that if you go above two for a state, it will throw an error back.

We will handle real errors in Chapter 5.

Please also remember Chapter 3 and are only very basic examples to prepare us to do 
some real Seam coding starting in chapter 5.